.TH "spum_ns2_ctx_max_payload" 9 "spum_ns2_ctx_max_payload" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spum_ns2_ctx_max_payload \- Determine the max length of the payload for a SPU message for a given cipher and hash alg context.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" spum_ns2_ctx_max_payload
.BI "(enum spu_cipher_alg cipher_alg "  ","
.BI "enum spu_cipher_mode cipher_mode "  ","
.BI "unsigned int blocksize "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cipher_alg" 12
The cipher algorithm
.IP "cipher_mode" 12
The cipher mode
.IP "blocksize" 12
The size of a block of data for this algo
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The max payload must be a multiple of the blocksize so that if a request is
too large to fit in a single SPU message, the request can be broken into
max_payload sized chunks. Each chunk must be a multiple of blocksize.
.SH "RETURN"
Max payload length in bytes
